FBIS4-17994 "drsov083_m_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-083 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 Tajikistan Deputy Chief of Militia Department, Family Shot Dead Deputy Chief of Militia Department, Family Shot Dead LD2804144694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1107 GMT 28 Apr 94 LD2804144694 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] A source close to law enforcement bodies reported to INTERFAX that in the night of 28 April deputy chief of the Tajikabad regional militia department Idibek Salomonov together with his wife and two children was shot dead from a sub-machine gun in his house (Tajikabad is located in the Garm group of Tajikistan's regions in the Republic's north-east). According to the source, the law enforcement bodies do not know anything about the motives of the murder. They are examining several versions, the results will be reported after the conclusion of the investigation.
